    {"id": 26, "question": "How do tensor parallel layers communicate gradients during the backward pass?", "answer": "Tensor parallel layers communicate gradients through all-reduce operations in the TP group. In megatron/core/tensor_parallel/, ColumnParallelLinear performs all-reduce of gradients in the backward pass when gather_output=False, while RowParallelLinear handles the reduction when input_is_parallel=True. The communication is implemented via custom autograd functions that perform async all-reduce during backward to overlap computation and communication. Sequence parallelism (when enabled) modifies this pattern by using reduce-scatter and all-gather operations instead of all-reduce to maintain sequence-distributed activations.", "file_line_refs": ["megatron/core/tensor_parallel/layers.py", "megatron/core/tensor_parallel/mappings.py"], "mdemg_context_used": True},
    {"id": 27, "question": "How does the DistributedDataParallel wrapper interact with the optimizer?", "answer": "DistributedDataParallel (megatron/core/distributed/distributed_data_parallel.py:22) wraps the model and handles gradient synchronization across DP ranks. It interacts with the optimizer through: 1) Registering gradient hooks that trigger all-reduce when gradients are ready; 2) Supporting gradient accumulation by controlling when all-reduce occurs; 3) Working with DistributedOptimizer for ZeRO-style sharding where gradients are reduced and scattered; 4) Configuration via DistributedDataParallelConfig (distributed_data_parallel_config.py:8). The optimizer receives synchronized gradients after DDP's backward pass completes.", "file_line_refs": ["megatron/core/distributed/distributed_data_parallel.py:22", "megatron/core/distributed/distributed_data_parallel_config.py:8"], "mdemg_context_used": True},
    {"id": 28, "question": "How does pipeline parallelism coordinate forward and backward passes across stages?", "answer": "Pipeline parallelism coordination is in megatron/core/pipeline_parallel/schedules.py. get_forward_backward_func (line 45) returns the appropriate schedule based on PP/VP configuration. Schedules include: 1) 1F1B (one forward, one backward) for basic pipelining; 2) Interleaved 1F1B for virtual pipeline parallelism; 3) Combined schedules in combined_1f1b.py. P2P communication (p2p_communication.py) handles tensor exchange between stages using P2PCommunicator. The schedule manages microbatch ordering, activation memory, and ensures proper gradient accumulation while minimizing pipeline bubbles.", "file_line_refs": ["megatron/core/pipeline_parallel/schedules.py:45", "megatron/core/pipeline_parallel/p2p_communication.py", "megatron/core/pipeline_parallel/combined_1f1b.py"], "mdemg_context_used": True},
    {"id": 29, "question": "How do MoE routers and token dispatchers work together?", "answer": "MoE routers and token dispatchers work in sequence within MoELayer (moe_layer.py:129). The Router (router.py:28) computes routing scores and selects top-k experts per token via TopKRouter (line 131). Token dispatchers (token_dispatcher.py) then handle the data movement: 1) MoEAllGatherTokenDispatcher (line 208) - gathers all tokens to all experts; 2) MoEAlltoAllTokenDispatcher (line 348) - point-to-point exchange for expert parallelism; 3) MoEFlexTokenDispatcher (line 1320) - flexible dispatch. The dispatcher routes tokens to selected experts, collects outputs, and combines them using routing weights.", "file_line_refs": ["megatron/core/transformer/moe/router.py:131", "megatron/core/transformer/moe/token_dispatcher.py:208", "megatron/core/transformer/moe/token_dispatcher.py:348", "megatron/core/transformer/moe/moe_layer.py:129"], "mdemg_context_used": True},
    {"id": 30, "question": "How does the distributed checkpointing system coordinate saves across ranks?", "answer": "Distributed checkpointing in megatron/core/dist_checkpointing/ coordinates saves through: 1) ShardedStateDict mapping tensors to distributed shards with metadata about TP/PP/DP placement; 2) Each rank saves only its local shard of each tensor; 3) Barrier synchronization ensures all ranks complete before finalizing; 4) Index files track which rank saved which shard; 5) Support for async saves to overlap checkpointing with training. The make_sharded_tensors_for_checkpoint and sharded_state_dict_default utilities in transformer/utils.py help construct proper shard mappings from model state.", "file_line_refs": ["megatron/core/dist_checkpointing/mapping.py", "megatron/core/transformer/utils.py", "megatron/core/transformer/module.py:58"], "mdemg_context_used": True},
